revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
<!-- Categories go at the bottom of this page and interwikis go in Wikidata. -->

This is a [[WP:hatnote|hatnote]] template that indicates the source page of a section transclusion and provides edit and history links for the source page (but does not actually transclude the section). For information on how to selectively transclude a particular section of one article into another, see [[WP:Selective transclusion]] and [[Help:Labeled section transclusion]].

==Usage==
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Transcluded section|source= |part= }}</syntaxhighlight>

==Examples==
{{demo|<nowiki>{{Transcluded section|source=Waffle}}</nowiki>}}

{{demo|<nowiki>{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=anything other than a positive value}}</nowiki>}}

{{demo|<nowiki>{{Transcluded section|source=Blintz|title=Blintzes blintzes blintzes}}</nowiki>}}

All of the following produce the same result:
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=yes}}
{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=YES}}
{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=y}}
{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=True}}
{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=1}}</syntaxhighlight>
{{Transcluded section|source=Pancake|part=yes}}

==TemplateData==
{{TemplateData header}}

<templatedata>
{
	"params": {
		"source": {
			"aliases": [
				"1"
			],
			"description": "The page name that you are transcluding from",
			"type": "wiki-page-name",
			"required": true
		},
		"part": {
			"description": "Changes the hatnote text from \"This section...\" to \"Part of this section...\"",
			"type": "boolean",
			"default": "0"
		},
		"title": {
			"description": "Overrides the displayed text of the article title",
			"type": "string",
			"default": "{{{1}}}"
		},
		"table": {
			"description": "Prepends \"This table\" if set",
			"suggestedvalues": [
				"yes"
			]
		}
	}
}</templatedata>

==See also==
*[[Wikipedia:Transclusion#Selective transclusion]] – how to transclude one or more sections of an article or project page into another
*[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3AWhatLinksHere&target=Template%3ATranscluded+section&namespace=0 Pages that link to "Template:Transcluded section" (articles)] (unsorted)
*{{tl|Transcluding article}} – transcludes one or more entire pages
**[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3AWhatLinksHere&target=Template%3ATranscluding+article&namespace=0 Pages that link to "Template:Transcluding article" (articles)] (unsorted)
*[[Wikipedia:Excerpts]]
**{{tl|Excerpt}} – transcludes a lead section or section and adds an appropriate hatnote
**[[:Category:Articles with excerpts]], or [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special%3AWhatLinksHere&target=Template%3AExcerpt&namespace=0 Pages that link to "Template:Excerpt" (articles)] (unsorted)

{{Hatnote templates}}

<includeonly>{{sandbox other||
<!-- Categories go below this line; interwikis go to Wikidata. -->
[[Category:Wikipedia page-section templates]]
[[Category:Hatnote templates]]<!--Not always used for lists.-->
[[Category:Hatnote templates for lists]]
[[Category:Transclude page content templates]]
}}</includeonly>

